  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the tandoor to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a blender or food processor, puree the roasted Anaheim chili peppers, garlic, mint leaves, heavy cream, melted butter, rice vinegar, paprika, salt, and black pepper until smooth.",
    "In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of oil over medium heat. Add the chicken and cook until browned on all sides and cooked through, about 10-12 minutes.",
    "Add the pureed sauce to the skillet and stir to coat the chicken. Simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "Serve the chicken hot, garnished with chopped fresh cilantro and additional mint leaves if desired."
